            <title><![CDATA[It’s not just about child mortality, life expectancy improved at all ages]]></title>
            <id>https://ourworldindata.org/its-not-just-about-child-mortality-life-expectancy-improved-at-all-ages</id>
            <link rel="alternate" href="https://ourworldindata.org/its-not-just-about-child-mortality-life-expectancy-improved-at-all-ages"/>
            <published>2020-09-23T11:00:00.000Z</published>
            <updated>2020-09-23T06:10:44.000Z</updated>
            <author><name>Max Roser</name></author>
            <summary><![CDATA[It’s often argued that life expectancy across the world has only increased because child mortality has fallen. But this untrue. The data shows that life expectancy has increased at all ages.<br><br><a href="https://ourworldindata.org/its-not-just-about-child-mortality-life-expectancy-improved-at-all-ages" target="_blank"><img src="https://ourworldindata.org/app/uploads/2020/03/Life-expectancy-by-age-in-the-UK-1700-to-2013-768x511.png"/></a>]]></summary>
